{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 09:35:23.643694", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and expectations\n- Design intent: Internal hosts should reach the external web servers (web_server_1_1 and web_server_1_2) only via a WireGuard VPN overlay. host_1 is the only preconfigured WireGuard client. All routers run RIP for infrastructure and LAN prefixes.\n- What we validated: End-to-end reachability to the external 20.0.0.0/24 LAN, HTTP access, VPN client state on host_1, and RIP routing tables on all routers.\n\nSummary of current network health\n- Core IP connectivity is healthy. All tested paths show 0% packet loss and low RTTs.\n- HTTP services on both web servers are reachable from both host_1 and host_2 with very low latency, indicating no congestion or packet loss.\n- RIP adjacencies and routing tables appear stable and consistent across routers.\n\nKey findings and evidence\n1) Policy violation: external web servers are reachable directly (bypassing VPN)\n- host_2 (which is not a VPN client) can ping and curl both web servers:\n  - Ping host_2 -> web_server_1_2 (20.0.0.4): 0% loss, avg ~1.98 ms.\n  - HTTP host_2 -> http://20.0.0.3 and http://20.0.0.4: successful, total times ~1.2–1.9 ms.\n- host_1 can also ping and curl both web servers with similarly low latency.\n- This contradicts the requirement that web_server_1_1 and web_server_1_2 be accessible only via VPN.\n\n2) The VPN overlay is not being used for web access by host_1\n- host_1 routing:\n  - Default route via 10.0.0.1 (eth0).\n  - wg0 only has 172.16.1.0/24 as connected.\n  - No route steering 20.0.0.0/24 into wg0.\n- WireGuard state on host_1:\n  - wg0 up, peer endpoint 20.0.0.2:51820, allowed-ips: 172.16.1.0/24.\n  - wg0 counters show RX/TX = 0 bytes, indicating no traffic traverses the tunnel during web access tests.\n\n3) Route leak of the server LAN into the internal RIP domain\n- external_router_1 routing table:\n  - C>* 20.0.0.0/24 is directly connected (br0).\n- gateway_router routing table:\n  - R>* 20.0.0.0/24 via 192.168.0.6 (eth2) — learned via RIP from external_router_1.\n- router1 and router2 routing tables:\n  - R>* 20.0.0.0/24 via gateway_router with expected metrics.\n- As a result, the entire internal network has a straightforward routed path to 20.0.0.0/24, enabling direct access to the web servers without using the VPN.\n\nAnomaly detection\n- Abnormal behavior: Web servers intended to be “VPN-only” are reachable directly from the internal network, including from non-VPN hosts.\n- Additional symptom: host_1’s WireGuard tunnel is up but idle for web traffic, confirming that traffic is not flowing through the VPN.\n\nFault localization\n- External routing edge: external_router_1 and gateway_router (RIP domain). 20.0.0.0/24 is being advertised and accepted within the internal RIP domain.\n- Endpoint client: host_1 WireGuard client configuration. Only 172.16.1.0/24 is permitted/steered into the tunnel; destinations in 20.0.0.0/24 are not.\n- Web servers themselves appear healthy and responsive; no fault indicated there.\n- The internal routers (router1, router2) are functioning as expected by propagating learned routes; their behavior is consistent with current RIP policy.\n\nRoot cause assessment\n- Primary cause: Routing/policy misalignment with design intent. The 20.0.0.0/24 server LAN is being distributed via RIP into the internal network, enabling direct routed access from all internal hosts and bypassing the VPN requirement.\n- Secondary cause on the client side: host_1’s WireGuard configuration does not steer 20.0.0.0/24 traffic into the VPN (allowed-ips limited to 172.16.1.0/24), so even the designated VPN client is not using the tunnel for web access.\n\nConclusion\n- The network is operational and healthy from a connectivity standpoint, but it violates the intended security/access policy. The server LAN 20.0.0.0/24 is reachable directly due to RIP advertisement and acceptance across the internal domain, and host_1’s VPN client configuration does not route traffic to the web servers through the VPN.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7477, "output_tokens": 3341, "total_tokens": 10818, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7296}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2304}}}
